name: Yoko Ono 🌳💚🌏
tweet: The human race has done that with many things. Like we wanted to fly, and invented aeroplanes. We wanted to see the other side of the moon, and we have. This time, we want to heal our planet, and bring peace to this world. We will.  #pebblepeople  https://t.co/RgV6tN6R52

name: Yoko Ono 🌳💚🌏
tweet: Send small pebbles to the world. Don’t make big splashes with large stones. That will attract people and the wrong people as well. Our quiet revolution will not make announcements, but one day will be accepted by all people as the norm of life.  #pebblepeople  https://t.co/UcGiNlPM5T

name: Yoko Ono 🌳💚🌏
tweet: Well, I thought we do affect each other on land, but I hadn’t realized that that was true in the ocean as well! What a blessing! Nature is making things so easy for us! So now I call ourselves the small pebble people.  #pebblepeople  https://t.co/kKawRMBMUa

name: Yoko Ono 🌳💚🌏
tweet: Happy Birthday Ringo! Peace and Love ✌️❤️ Lots of love, yoko  @ringostarrmusic #happybirthdayringo #peaceandlove  https://t.co/j7mb04PbGF

name: Yoko Ono 🌳💚🌏
tweet: Two scientists who were researching the effect of waves in the ocean for two years, came to the conclusion that the smallest stimulus to the water be it a drop of a pebble, or a child splashing the water at the shore, affects the whole ocean, each time.  #pebblepeople  https://t.co/stBDjX2CbP

name: Yoko Ono 🌳💚🌏
tweet: PEBBLE PEOPLE, 2010 We want to heal our planet, and bring peace to this world. We will.  #pebblepeople  https://t.co/Fj2UJ5SNa7

name: Yoko Ono 🌳💚🌏
tweet: CUT PIECE, 1964 There was a long silence between one person coming up and the next person coming up. And I said it's a fantastic, beautiful music, you know? Ba-ba-ba, cut! Ba-ba-ba, cut! Beautiful poetry, actually.  https://t.co/jYPSEplsed

name: Yoko Ono 🌳💚🌏
tweet: CUT PIECE, 1964 I realized that when somebody's cutting you – geometrically, it's a line. But our body is a curve. And they're trying to cut the curve with a line, which is very strange. And that's what they do in life.  https://t.co/KzmGUi2H6R

name: Yoko Ono 🌳💚🌏
tweet: CUT PIECE, 1964 We usually give something with a purpose of ours.But I wanted to see what they would take.  https://t.co/3swaM7OYHP

name: Yoko Ono 🌳💚🌏
tweet: CUT PIECE, 1964 When I do Cut Piece, I get into a trance, and so I don't feel too frightened. There's several layers of meanings. I was saying, 'hey, you're doing this to women'. By not fighting, we show them that there's a whole world which could exist by being peaceful.  https://t.co/8atcKXc0Qi
